{
  "texts": [
    "This iterative process continues until the desired output length is reached or an end-of-sequence token is produced.",
    "The execution lifecycle is governed by three families of pluggable policies.",
    "Each policy operates on a read-only snapshot of recent system performance metrics, such as queue depth, round-trip time (RTT), time-per-output-token (TPOT), and acceptance rate.",
    "Request Routing Policy These policies determine how incoming requests are distributed across clusters, supporting a variety of load-balancing strategies in multi-cluster deployments.",
    "Common implementations include random selection, round-robin scheduling, and the Join-the-Shortest-Queue (JSQ) policy."
  ]
}